1
00:00:00,104 --> 00:00:04,957
SOLD OUT ON YOU

2
00:00:04,981 --> 00:00:06,973
PRODUCTION SUPPORTED BY:
MINISTRY OF CULTURE, SPORTS AND TOURISM,
KOREA CREATIVE CONTENT AGENCY

3
00:00:06,997 --> 00:00:08,082
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

4
00:00:08,165 --> 00:00:09,417
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

5
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:10,918
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

6
00:00:11,002 --> 00:00:11,981
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

7
00:00:13,801 --> 00:00:14,885
HIT HOMESHOPPING

8
00:00:14,969 --> 00:00:17,221
- How many times do I have to tell you?
- Sorry, ma'am.

9
00:00:17,304 --> 00:00:18,806
- The product is so good!
- Of course!

10
00:00:18,889 --> 00:00:21,225
Dam Ye-jin's a good seller,
so tell them to get her!

11
00:00:21,308 --> 00:00:23,394
They said to change them all to big ones.

12
00:00:25,896 --> 00:00:26,731
Coming through.

13
00:00:28,566 --> 00:00:30,234
We're up next after Dam Ye-jin, right?

14
00:00:30,317 --> 00:00:31,736
Yes, you're up next.

15
00:00:33,779 --> 00:00:34,947
Hello, ma'am.

16
00:00:43,497 --> 00:00:45,458
- Sir, you have to check this.
- Go do your thing.

17
00:00:45,541 --> 00:00:46,375
- Thank you.
- Zoom in.

18
00:00:46,459 --> 00:00:47,543
Okay.

19
00:00:47,626 --> 00:00:49,503
We're done preparing the samples.

20
00:00:49,587 --> 00:00:51,338
Hello.

21
00:01:01,307 --> 00:01:02,349
- Hey.
- Yes?

22
00:01:02,933 --> 00:01:05,644
Is it always a mess like this in studio?

23
00:01:06,729 --> 00:01:07,646
Sorry about that, sir.

24
00:01:08,189 --> 00:01:09,023
Go.

25
00:01:09,106 --> 00:01:09,940
I'm sorry.

26
00:01:11,901 --> 00:01:14,528
It's a complete disaster on set.

27
00:01:15,905 --> 00:01:19,825
Wait, we're about to go live,
but where on earth is Ye-jin?

28
00:01:22,453 --> 00:01:23,704
Dam Ye-jin's not picking up.

29
00:01:24,413 --> 00:01:25,498
What?

30
00:01:25,581 --> 00:01:27,249
What did you just say, Ms. Eom?

31
00:01:27,333 --> 00:01:28,667
We may have to go on without her.

32
00:01:28,751 --> 00:01:30,878
How can we go live without the main host?

33
00:01:30,961 --> 00:01:32,254
I don't know! What do we do?

34
00:01:33,214 --> 00:01:34,799
<i>All right, everyone.</i>

35
00:01:34,882 --> 00:01:36,509
<i>The product I'll be introducing today</i>

36
00:01:36,592 --> 00:01:37,718
<i>is none other than</i>

37
00:01:37,802 --> 00:01:39,804
all-purpose gloves for cleaning!

38
00:01:39,887 --> 00:01:42,348
Don't they look as adorable as I do?

39
00:01:42,431 --> 00:01:43,557
Woof, woof!

40
00:01:45,726 --> 00:01:47,853
They're 100% made in Korea.
Zero synthetic fibers!

41
00:01:47,937 --> 00:01:49,146
Perfect for removing stains!

42
00:01:49,230 --> 00:01:50,231
They're powerful!

43
00:01:53,943 --> 00:01:56,278
Ms. Eom, let's just roll
a recorded segment right now.

44
00:01:56,362 --> 00:01:58,739
If something goes wrong on air,
we'll all be done for.

45
00:01:58,823 --> 00:01:59,990
<i>And that's why…</i>

46
00:02:00,741 --> 00:02:03,869
Sir, we'll go straight into the demo.

47
00:02:03,953 --> 00:02:07,706
<i>We're not getting many calls,
so how about starting the demo right away?</i>

48
00:02:08,541 --> 00:02:11,794
Now, I'll demonstrate
the power of these all-purpose gloves.

49
00:02:11,877 --> 00:02:12,711
Dust!

50
00:02:12,795 --> 00:02:16,465
<i>Oh, my God! Jesus!
Now, let's try removing grease!</i>

51
00:02:20,594 --> 00:02:21,428
All right!

52
00:02:22,471 --> 00:02:24,974
All right! Okay! Like this!

53
00:02:25,683 --> 00:02:26,684
Okay!

54
00:02:27,935 --> 00:02:30,437
<i>Of course, it's hard
to get rid of grease easily.</i>

55
00:02:30,938 --> 00:02:32,356
You, the floor manager. Come here.

56
00:02:33,524 --> 00:02:35,109
All right!

57
00:02:35,192 --> 00:02:37,194
Hey, why isn't this coming off?

58
00:02:37,278 --> 00:02:39,530
You're supposed to wet it first.

59
00:02:39,613 --> 00:02:42,950
All right, our final attack! Hey, grease!

60
00:02:43,033 --> 00:02:43,868
Take this!

61
00:02:51,625 --> 00:02:52,835
Hey, are you okay?

62
00:02:57,006 --> 00:02:58,215
These all-purpose gloves

63
00:02:58,299 --> 00:03:00,926
may not be that effective,
but aren't they charming?

64
00:03:02,511 --> 00:03:03,888
We're losing all the calls!

65
00:03:03,971 --> 00:03:05,222
Please do something, Mr. Hwang!

66
00:03:05,306 --> 00:03:06,515
Well, let's calm down first.

67
00:03:06,599 --> 00:03:07,474
"Calm down"?

68
00:03:08,184 --> 00:03:09,727
Does it look like I can calm down?

69
00:03:09,810 --> 00:03:11,187
I put my faith in Ms. Dam

70
00:03:11,270 --> 00:03:13,898
and had everyone work overtime
for an entire month

71
00:03:13,981 --> 00:03:16,192
to pull together
every bit of stock we could!

72
00:03:16,275 --> 00:03:19,528
Enough. If today's show flops,
I'm filing a lawsuit right away.

73
00:03:19,612 --> 00:03:22,114
Ma'am, there's a big problem!

74
00:03:22,198 --> 00:03:23,991
Our sales are a bigger problem. Look.

75
00:03:24,074 --> 00:03:24,992
LIVE ORDER STATUS

76
00:03:26,535 --> 00:03:28,913
Mr. Hwang, you go in
and do the demo instead.

77
00:03:28,996 --> 00:03:31,749
Tell our host to just talk
and not do anything else.

78
00:03:31,832 --> 00:03:33,626
What? Me?

79
00:03:33,709 --> 00:03:34,585
What?

80
00:03:35,085 --> 00:03:37,087
You can't do it? I guess he can't do it.

81
00:03:37,171 --> 00:03:39,256
Then, what do we do? I'll go. I can do it.

82
00:03:39,340 --> 00:03:42,509
Just make quick cuts
and flash the "Almost Sold Out" captions.

83
00:03:42,593 --> 00:03:44,803
And we'll all take a trip
to the Standards Commission.

84
00:03:44,887 --> 00:03:45,846
Move!

85
00:03:45,930 --> 00:03:48,390
Let go of me!
Let me get on air before they fire me!

86
00:03:48,474 --> 00:03:50,226
All right, I'll get on standby!

87
00:03:51,310 --> 00:03:52,561
For crying out loud!

88
00:03:53,103 --> 00:03:56,315
Who is it? Whose phone is ringing
when we're live…

89
00:04:01,362 --> 00:04:03,113
Hello?

90
00:04:04,406 --> 00:04:05,449
<i>Okay, stand by.</i>

91
00:04:09,787 --> 00:04:10,621
<i>Action.</i>

92
00:04:11,205 --> 00:04:13,207
Everyone, were you looking for me?

93
00:04:13,290 --> 00:04:15,918
I'm greeting you
from a special location today.

94
00:04:16,001 --> 00:04:18,254
I'm your home shopping host, Dam Ye-jin.

95
00:04:18,337 --> 00:04:19,380
Can you guess where I am?

96
00:04:19,463 --> 00:04:22,633
I'm at the highest building in Korea,

97
00:04:22,716 --> 00:04:24,218
the Lux Tower.

98
00:04:28,222 --> 00:04:30,266
Lux Tower!

99
00:04:30,349 --> 00:04:31,642
- She's finally here.
- <i>Yeah!</i>

100
00:04:32,726 --> 00:04:34,311
<i>Why am I here?</i>

101
00:04:34,395 --> 00:04:35,688
<i>Everyone.</i>

102
00:04:35,771 --> 00:04:37,314
- What?
<i>- Look here.</i>

103
00:04:37,398 --> 00:04:39,149
<i>- See this window?</i>
- This is incredible.

104
00:04:39,233 --> 00:04:41,485
This is a year's worth of built-up grime!

105
00:04:48,075 --> 00:04:49,618
It's crazy, right?

106
00:04:49,702 --> 00:04:53,163
Ordinary cleaning products
won't be able to remove this.

107
00:04:53,247 --> 00:04:55,332
All right. Watch this.

108
00:04:56,166 --> 00:04:57,793
I'll spray this cleaner.

109
00:04:59,295 --> 00:05:00,129
All right.

110
00:05:01,046 --> 00:05:02,881
Everyone, do you see this?

111
00:05:02,965 --> 00:05:09,138
I'm wiping pretty hard,
but look at how this grime is still there.

112
00:05:09,221 --> 00:05:10,055
But now,

113
00:05:11,056 --> 00:05:13,809
<i>I'll show you the power
of these all-purpose gloves.</i>

114
00:05:16,270 --> 00:05:19,815
<i>All I did was soak these in water,
and I wrung them out.</i>

115
00:05:19,898 --> 00:05:22,776
You might wonder, "Did she spray them
with bleach or cleaner?"

116
00:05:25,112 --> 00:05:26,238
How nice and damp.

117
00:05:26,321 --> 00:05:29,533
Did you see? There's only water on it.
Now, look carefully.

118
00:05:32,578 --> 00:05:34,246
<i>Where did it all go?</i>

119
00:05:34,329 --> 00:05:37,791
<i>Everyone, you really have to
try this out for yourself.</i>

120
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:39,543
I'm sure you all know what this is.

121
00:05:39,626 --> 00:05:43,172
Since it lasts even through greasy meals,
they call it "paint lipstick."

122
00:05:43,257 --> 00:05:45,885
DAM YE-JIN

123
00:05:45,966 --> 00:05:47,426
Hey, what are you doing?

124
00:05:47,509 --> 00:05:49,970
Everyone, if I can't erase this,

125
00:05:50,054 --> 00:05:51,513
I'm going to get in big trouble.

126
00:05:51,597 --> 00:05:54,683
<i>- Will these all-purpose gloves save me?</i>
- Geez, this was expensive!

127
00:05:54,767 --> 00:05:56,435
<i>Just wait and watch.</i>

128
00:05:56,518 --> 00:05:57,478
<i>All right.</i>

129
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:01,774
What do you think?
It's spotless, isn't it?

130
00:06:02,608 --> 00:06:04,193
That is amazing.

131
00:06:04,276 --> 00:06:07,362
Everyone, with these all-purpose gloves,
I just got acknowledged

132
00:06:07,446 --> 00:06:10,491
<i>by a professional building cleaner
with 30 years of experience.</i>

133
00:06:10,574 --> 00:06:12,993
<i>These gloves will instantly make you
a professional cleaner!</i>

134
00:06:13,077 --> 00:06:16,080
<i>You'll get a 10% discount
only during this broadcast,</i>

135
00:06:16,163 --> 00:06:18,749
<i>so place your order now
through our mobile app.</i>

136
00:06:18,832 --> 00:06:20,501
If I had these, I'd be in the majors.

137
00:06:20,584 --> 00:06:22,753
Hey, they're not those kinds of gloves!

138
00:06:22,836 --> 00:06:24,838
Yes, the all-purpose gloves?

139
00:06:24,922 --> 00:06:27,883
They grab every bit
of dust and grime there is.

140
00:06:28,592 --> 00:06:31,386
Even fine dust you can't see
is all trapped right in here.

141
00:06:31,970 --> 00:06:35,265
And it's waterproof inside,
so your hands will stay perfectly dry.

142
00:06:35,349 --> 00:06:38,435
They're also really easy to clean.

143
00:06:38,519 --> 00:06:39,728
A large size?

144
00:06:40,729 --> 00:06:44,400
If you were worried about getting
your hands wet or dirty while cleaning,

145
00:06:44,483 --> 00:06:46,318
<i>you don't have to worry about that now.</i>

146
00:06:47,152 --> 00:06:49,113
<i>Do you see how nice and dry my hands are?</i>

147
00:06:49,905 --> 00:06:50,906
<i>Now,</i>

148
00:06:50,989 --> 00:06:56,245
<i>let me highlight the key features
of these all-purpose gloves once more.</i>

149
00:06:56,328 --> 00:07:01,834
Yeah, didn't I tell you?
You can put your faith in Dam Ye-jin.

150
00:07:04,253 --> 00:07:08,090
Dam Ye-jin really knew what she was doing.

151
00:07:08,674 --> 00:07:10,801
All right, the second set
is almost sold out as well.

152
00:07:10,884 --> 00:07:12,386
We're probably going to end early.

153
00:07:12,469 --> 00:07:13,762
Make sure the next one's ready.

154
00:07:13,846 --> 00:07:16,515
Everyone, this is going
to be sold out within one minute.

155
00:07:16,598 --> 00:07:19,435
So hurry.
I'll throw it back to the studio now.

156
00:07:19,518 --> 00:07:21,979
This has been your host, Dam Ye-jin.
Thank you!

157
00:07:23,147 --> 00:07:24,231
Cut!

158
00:07:25,816 --> 00:07:27,359
I thought I was going to die earlier!

159
00:07:28,444 --> 00:07:30,112
Wait. Hold on.

160
00:07:30,904 --> 00:07:32,489
- Hang on. Let me see.
- What is it?

161
00:07:33,198 --> 00:07:34,032
Just a moment.

162
00:07:35,534 --> 00:07:36,869
Please…

163
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:41,206
<i>We're completely
sold out of today's stock!</i>

164
00:07:41,290 --> 00:07:42,124
<i>Sold out!</i>

165
00:07:45,127 --> 00:07:47,546
Everyone, they said we're sold out!

166
00:07:47,629 --> 00:07:48,464
Sold out?

167
00:07:48,547 --> 00:07:49,548
Sir!

168
00:07:49,631 --> 00:07:50,632
Sold out!

169
00:07:50,716 --> 00:07:52,634
- Great job!
- We're sold out!

170
00:07:53,510 --> 00:07:54,928
Sir!

171
00:07:57,723 --> 00:07:59,016
- Sold out!
- Sold out!

172
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:02,978
Sold out!

173
00:08:04,354 --> 00:08:05,939
We're sold out!

174
00:08:06,899 --> 00:08:09,401
Sold out! Thank you!

175
00:08:09,485 --> 00:08:10,319
Thank you!

176
00:08:10,402 --> 00:08:16,867
SOLD OUT ON YOU

177
00:08:48,899 --> 00:08:52,903
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE

178
00:08:59,701 --> 00:09:01,870
Mechoori, thank you!

179
00:09:04,164 --> 00:09:05,165
Sorry?

180
00:09:05,249 --> 00:09:09,044
Thanks for taking Changsik on a walk.

181
00:09:09,127 --> 00:09:10,879
I didn't. He just followed me.

182
00:09:10,963 --> 00:09:12,047
CHANGSIK
HE DOESN'T BITE

183
00:09:12,130 --> 00:09:14,633
- And that mutt--
- His name's Changsik.

184
00:09:15,384 --> 00:09:17,427
Yes, Changsik.
He needs to be put on a leash.

185
00:09:17,511 --> 00:09:19,721
He'll grow big enough
to high-five you soon.

186
00:09:19,805 --> 00:09:21,640
What? What's that?

187
00:09:23,058 --> 00:09:24,351
Well…

188
00:09:25,852 --> 00:09:27,437
It's like patty-cake…

189
00:09:33,777 --> 00:09:34,820
Anyway,

190
00:09:34,903 --> 00:09:37,114
it's dangerous to let him
follow anyone around.

191
00:09:37,197 --> 00:09:39,700
Come on. What do you mean "anyone"?

192
00:09:39,783 --> 00:09:43,579
Changsik only likes you, Mechoori.

193
00:09:43,662 --> 00:09:45,497
- He does.
- Whenever he sees you,

194
00:09:45,581 --> 00:09:46,957
he follows you around!

195
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:50,627
- And he follows and follows!
- And he follows and follows!

196
00:09:51,295 --> 00:09:53,171
I'm not Mechoori.

197
00:09:53,255 --> 00:09:54,089
What?

198
00:09:55,173 --> 00:09:56,466
It's Matthew Lee.

199
00:09:57,509 --> 00:09:59,678
Right. Matthew…

200
00:09:59,761 --> 00:10:01,597
- Mechoori!
- Mechoori!

201
00:10:02,598 --> 00:10:03,599
Hey, Mechoori.

202
00:10:03,682 --> 00:10:05,267
Take these and steam them.

203
00:10:05,976 --> 00:10:07,603
It's fine. I have a lot of food at home.

204
00:10:07,686 --> 00:10:09,438
Fine, I'll throw them away.

205
00:10:09,521 --> 00:10:11,398
Okay, fine.

206
00:10:11,481 --> 00:10:12,482
You're going to eat them?

207
00:10:13,442 --> 00:10:15,777
This is too much.
Do you have some for yourself?

208
00:10:15,861 --> 00:10:18,488
Of course. I have tons left.

209
00:10:22,993 --> 00:10:24,369
All right. Just this once then.

210
00:10:27,331 --> 00:10:28,832
Mechoori!

211
00:10:28,915 --> 00:10:31,501
- Hey, Mechoori!
- Hey. Mechoori!

212
00:10:31,585 --> 00:10:32,753
Mechoori…

213
00:10:35,213 --> 00:10:36,923
NO DATA AVAILABLE

214
00:10:37,007 --> 00:10:38,091
NO INPUT SIGNAL

215
00:10:38,175 --> 00:10:39,968
See? It's not working.

216
00:10:40,052 --> 00:10:41,637
The Wi-Fi must be disconnected.

217
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:42,971
Why is it so bad?

218
00:10:43,055 --> 00:10:45,307
Then call your service provider.

219
00:10:45,390 --> 00:10:47,225
I'll be already dead
by the time they arrive.

220
00:10:48,185 --> 00:10:49,770
- They'll arrive before that.
- What?

221
00:10:50,979 --> 00:10:52,689
Mechoori, where are you going?

222
00:10:52,773 --> 00:10:53,857
Mechoori! Hey!

223
00:10:56,693 --> 00:10:58,111
Come and sit down.

224
00:10:58,945 --> 00:10:59,780
Sit down, everyone.

225
00:11:00,405 --> 00:11:02,824
- Song Ga-in! Song Ga-in!
- Song Ga-in! Song Ga-in!

226
00:11:02,908 --> 00:11:03,742
Have a seat.

227
00:11:05,952 --> 00:11:07,954
Are you here to see Song Ga-in too?

228
00:11:08,455 --> 00:11:10,082
Come and sit down.

229
00:11:22,094 --> 00:11:23,428
Geez.

230
00:11:28,392 --> 00:11:29,226
Is it working?

231
00:11:29,309 --> 00:11:30,310
Go look.

232
00:11:31,103 --> 00:11:32,687
No!

233
00:11:32,771 --> 00:11:34,064
Move it to the right.

234
00:11:34,147 --> 00:11:35,440
Just a bit more.

235
00:11:39,069 --> 00:11:40,278
What about now?

236
00:11:40,362 --> 00:11:42,197
BEST TROT SINGER
SONG GA-IN

237
00:11:42,906 --> 00:11:44,282
Just a bit more!

238
00:11:44,366 --> 00:11:45,659
Just a little more.

239
00:11:56,795 --> 00:11:58,130
And now?

240
00:12:00,340 --> 00:12:01,216
It's working!

241
00:12:01,299 --> 00:12:02,801
It's working now!

242
00:12:07,556 --> 00:12:09,850
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE SENIOR CENTER OPENING

243
00:12:13,228 --> 00:12:14,396
Good job!

244
00:12:14,479 --> 00:12:16,773
- This is awesome!
- It's working really well!

245
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:19,151
It looks nice and clear.

246
00:12:22,779 --> 00:12:25,115
Gosh, thank you so much.

247
00:12:25,198 --> 00:12:26,450
You can head back now.

248
00:12:26,533 --> 00:12:28,452
Leave it. I'll put that away.

249
00:12:28,535 --> 00:12:30,203
It's fine. And one more thing.

250
00:12:30,287 --> 00:12:33,248
That's the last time
I'm going up on the roof.

251
00:12:33,331 --> 00:12:34,207
Here…

252
00:12:34,291 --> 00:12:35,459
I'm off.

253
00:12:41,047 --> 00:12:42,340
- Mechoori!
- Mechoori!

254
00:12:50,807 --> 00:12:52,100
He's good at driving too.

255
00:12:55,645 --> 00:12:56,938
Look at him.

256
00:12:57,022 --> 00:12:57,856
He's so prickly.

257
00:12:57,939 --> 00:13:00,734
He never says yes with a smile.

258
00:13:00,817 --> 00:13:01,943
That young brat.

259
00:13:02,027 --> 00:13:03,737
Hey, you old brat!

260
00:13:04,321 --> 00:13:07,991
Even if he speaks curtly,
he's been helping us with everything.

261
00:13:08,074 --> 00:13:09,826
You shouldn't treat him like that.

262
00:13:09,910 --> 00:13:10,994
- He's right!
- Yeah!

263
00:13:11,077 --> 00:13:12,204
ONE DAY
AT JONG-IL'S COW SHED

264
00:13:12,287 --> 00:13:13,705
One, two, three, pull!

265
00:13:13,788 --> 00:13:15,248
Pull!

266
00:13:15,332 --> 00:13:17,918
Okay. One, two, three, pull!

267
00:13:22,881 --> 00:13:24,424
- The teeth look fine.
- That's a relief.

268
00:13:24,508 --> 00:13:26,134
UNERUPTED TEETH
STILL COVERED BY GUMS

269
00:13:26,218 --> 00:13:27,636
That was exhausting, wasn't it?

270
00:13:27,719 --> 00:13:31,306
Mechoori's better than you
at pulling calves now.

271
00:13:31,389 --> 00:13:32,807
Hey, don't be stupid.

272
00:13:32,891 --> 00:13:35,644
Don't you know how many calves
I pulled at your shed?

273
00:13:35,727 --> 00:13:38,063
You don't need to deliver them anymore.

274
00:13:38,146 --> 00:13:40,398
Mechoori's really come into his own
handling them now!

275
00:13:40,482 --> 00:13:44,236
Geez, do you know why I'm asking
Mechoori to pull your calves?

276
00:13:44,319 --> 00:13:49,241
I pity the calves that will have to see
that ugly face of yours their whole lives.

277
00:13:49,324 --> 00:13:53,036
I wanted to let them
see Mechoori's handsome face for a moment.

278
00:13:53,119 --> 00:13:53,995
Are you done talking?

279
00:13:54,079 --> 00:13:55,121
Nope, not at all.

280
00:13:55,205 --> 00:13:57,707
Have you forgotten
when you used to get beaten up

281
00:13:57,791 --> 00:13:58,708
all the time?

282
00:13:58,792 --> 00:14:00,752
Bring it on then. How about a bull fight?

283
00:14:00,836 --> 00:14:02,045
Go ahead.

284
00:14:02,128 --> 00:14:03,296
This is my last time

285
00:14:03,380 --> 00:14:04,798
helping you out in the shed.

286
00:14:07,634 --> 00:14:09,344
- I'm off.
- Thanks.

287
00:14:10,345 --> 00:14:12,347
Wait, there's one more!

288
00:14:12,430 --> 00:14:13,849
Come on! Hurry!

289
00:14:13,932 --> 00:14:14,975
Come here.

290
00:14:15,058 --> 00:14:16,768
Damn it.

291
00:14:18,019 --> 00:14:19,229
That's not all.

292
00:14:19,312 --> 00:14:21,439
He even chopped all your firewood for you.

293
00:14:21,523 --> 00:14:25,402
ON ANOTHER DAY,
HOUSE CALL FOR FIREWOOD CHOPPING

294
00:14:25,485 --> 00:14:26,778
Geez!

295
00:14:27,904 --> 00:14:28,864
Please…

296
00:14:29,990 --> 00:14:31,324
He's right!

297
00:14:31,408 --> 00:14:32,868
And you remember that other time?

298
00:14:33,451 --> 00:14:36,955
AND ON ANOTHER DAY,
VILLAGE HALL BEEHIVE REMOVAL

299
00:14:37,038 --> 00:14:38,790
Grab the end. It's okay.

300
00:14:38,874 --> 00:14:40,458
- Find your balance.
- Don't be scared.

301
00:14:40,542 --> 00:14:42,460
DEOKPUNG COMMUNITY CENTER

302
00:14:45,213 --> 00:14:46,298
Yeah, you're right.

303
00:14:46,381 --> 00:14:49,092
That's right! That day was really fun too.

304
00:14:50,260 --> 00:14:53,805
AND ON YET ANOTHER DAY,
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE'S KIMCHI-MAKING DAY

305
00:14:53,889 --> 00:14:56,057
Mechoori, open up.

306
00:14:59,019 --> 00:15:01,396
<i>"It's Matthew Lee, not Mechoori."</i>

307
00:15:02,647 --> 00:15:03,481
And there's that.

308
00:15:03,565 --> 00:15:05,317
Why aren't you mentioning that?

309
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:07,152
You know. That.

310
00:15:07,861 --> 00:15:10,655
TYPHOON ROMEO HITS DEOKPUNG VILLAGE

311
00:15:13,825 --> 00:15:15,827
Oh, come on.

312
00:15:15,911 --> 00:15:16,786
Damn it.

313
00:15:18,288 --> 00:15:19,956
And you still think he's prickly?

314
00:15:21,458 --> 00:15:23,418
I do remember something else.

315
00:15:23,501 --> 00:15:25,587
Our village might fly away at this rate!

316
00:15:25,670 --> 00:15:27,213
This is insane.

317
00:15:27,839 --> 00:15:29,507
Come on. Let's close the window.

318
00:15:30,175 --> 00:15:31,885
- Close it.
- It's not closing.

319
00:15:32,469 --> 00:15:36,973
TYPHOON JULIET HITS DEOKPUNG VILLAGE

320
00:15:42,687 --> 00:15:43,563
Come on!

321
00:15:44,189 --> 00:15:45,023
Right!

322
00:15:45,106 --> 00:15:47,859
We would've been in huge trouble
if it weren't for him.

323
00:15:47,943 --> 00:15:50,362
- But he wasn't like this from the start.
- Yeah.

324
00:15:50,445 --> 00:15:52,447
He's finally become a bit nice.

325
00:15:52,530 --> 00:15:54,199
What did I tell you?

326
00:15:54,783 --> 00:15:57,452
Mechoori's like streusel bread.

327
00:15:57,535 --> 00:16:00,747
Rough on the outside
but soft on the inside.

328
00:16:02,415 --> 00:16:03,416
Streusel bread!

329
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:06,211
You're right. Should I go buy
some streusel bread?

330
00:16:06,294 --> 00:16:08,296
- Sounds nice.
- How many? Two?

331
00:16:08,380 --> 00:16:10,465
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE BUS STOP

332
00:16:12,634 --> 00:16:14,052
Mechoori, stop!

333
00:16:14,135 --> 00:16:15,929
I'm going to get off here!

334
00:16:21,810 --> 00:16:23,561
Thanks.

335
00:16:26,314 --> 00:16:28,316
When are you heading back?

336
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,193
I'm not the village bus driver.

337
00:16:30,276 --> 00:16:31,778
I'm heading back around 4:30 p.m.

338
00:16:31,861 --> 00:16:33,363
You can wait for me then or whatever.

339
00:16:36,408 --> 00:16:37,409
I said 4:30 p.m., okay?

340
00:16:37,492 --> 00:16:39,369
Okay, 4:30 p.m. See you later.

341
00:16:41,955 --> 00:16:43,206
Bye.

342
00:17:01,057 --> 00:17:02,642
<i>A simultaneous live broadcast?</i>

343
00:17:02,726 --> 00:17:03,935
You know how Dam Ye-jin is.

344
00:17:04,019 --> 00:17:06,104
Once she's set on something,
she stops at nothing.

345
00:17:06,604 --> 00:17:09,357
My heart was racing,
and I was nervous and anxious all morning.

346
00:17:09,441 --> 00:17:11,026
I'm filing a workers' comp claim!

347
00:17:11,109 --> 00:17:12,819
You have to add my name as well.

348
00:17:12,902 --> 00:17:14,988
The partner company people
threatened to sue me!

349
00:17:15,071 --> 00:17:18,783
- I really--
- Okay, I get it! You did great.

350
00:17:18,867 --> 00:17:20,535
Hey, it all ended well today.

351
00:17:20,618 --> 00:17:22,912
You know how intense Dam Ye-jin is.

352
00:17:24,914 --> 00:17:26,082
But what's with her anyway?

353
00:17:26,708 --> 00:17:28,752
I know she's popular,
but she's filming commercials<i>…</i>

354
00:17:28,835 --> 00:17:30,295
WHETHER IT'S RAIN OR SNOW
IONA

355
00:17:32,172 --> 00:17:33,590
<i>She's a brand ambassador,</i>

356
00:17:33,673 --> 00:17:36,593
<i>and she's even appearing on </i>Running Man.

357
00:17:36,676 --> 00:17:38,094
<i>What is she even doing on there?</i>

358
00:17:38,178 --> 00:17:40,305
What is she going to do? What?

359
00:17:42,432 --> 00:17:45,185
Superstar Dam! Gosh, no need to be sorry!

360
00:17:45,268 --> 00:17:46,519
No, it was good!

361
00:17:46,603 --> 00:17:49,981
Gosh, a true professional
would never complain about that…

362
00:17:52,859 --> 00:17:54,152
Lunch?

363
00:17:55,195 --> 00:17:56,029
I'll come by myself.

364
00:17:56,780 --> 00:17:58,114
Hurry? Okay, I'm coming.

365
00:18:03,286 --> 00:18:04,120
Are you all right?

366
00:18:04,704 --> 00:18:06,581
Weren't you even scared?

367
00:18:06,664 --> 00:18:08,291
Gosh, I'm more afraid of leftover stock.

368
00:18:08,374 --> 00:18:10,502
I'm late for an engagement,
so I'll get going.

369
00:18:10,585 --> 00:18:11,544
Ye-jin!

370
00:18:11,628 --> 00:18:12,837
- Hello.
- Hello.

371
00:18:12,921 --> 00:18:14,964
- Hello.
- Could we have an autograph?

372
00:18:15,048 --> 00:18:16,716
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

373
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:17,884
I loved the show.

374
00:18:17,967 --> 00:18:20,220
I'm a huge fan.
Could I get a photo with you?

375
00:18:20,845 --> 00:18:21,763
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

376
00:18:21,846 --> 00:18:22,931
I'm a huge fan.

377
00:18:41,533 --> 00:18:42,951
Here's your dish.

378
00:18:43,034 --> 00:18:44,160
Thank you.

379
00:18:46,621 --> 00:18:48,081
Please enjoy.

380
00:18:48,164 --> 00:18:49,541
Thank you.

381
00:18:49,624 --> 00:18:51,835
Lucky you. You always arrive
right when the food comes.

382
00:18:55,839 --> 00:18:56,965
I'm sorry.

383
00:18:57,841 --> 00:19:01,261
But I practically
flew over here to see you.

384
00:19:04,764 --> 00:19:05,598
Eat up.

385
00:19:10,979 --> 00:19:12,480
Let's watch a movie later.

386
00:19:12,564 --> 00:19:13,898
We can go after we eat.

387
00:19:13,982 --> 00:19:15,441
You said you wanted to see this.

388
00:19:17,318 --> 00:19:18,570
I'm sorry.

389
00:19:18,653 --> 00:19:20,864
Our new program's launching tomorrow,

390
00:19:21,823 --> 00:19:24,409
so I have to head back
to work after dinner…

391
00:19:31,166 --> 00:19:33,209
You know how many surgeries I do each day?

392
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:37,714
I'm probably
one of the busiest people in Korea.

393
00:19:37,797 --> 00:19:38,840
But "busy" is something…

394
00:19:38,923 --> 00:19:40,800
<i>What's with this knife? It's light.</i>

395
00:19:40,884 --> 00:19:42,677
<i>It cuts well. And it's cute.</i>

396
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:45,221
<i>This would be nice for a fancy meal.</i>

397
00:19:45,305 --> 00:19:47,557
<i>Yeah, this is perfect.</i>

398
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:49,100
- Are you listening to me?
<i>- You pass.</i>

399
00:19:49,184 --> 00:19:51,102
<i>I'm sure our customers would love this.</i>

400
00:19:51,603 --> 00:19:52,687
<i>Should I try to sell it?</i>

401
00:19:52,770 --> 00:19:54,355
Let's break up.

402
00:19:59,652 --> 00:20:01,738
Ui-seok, are you angry?
(Watch on www.kisskh.la or www.kisskh.id to support Admin)

403
00:20:01,821 --> 00:20:03,907
I'll postpone the meeting.
Let's go see the movie.

404
00:20:03,990 --> 00:20:07,869
Forget it. You're just going
to keep stepping out to take calls.

405
00:20:07,952 --> 00:20:09,037
No,

406
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:10,288
I'll really--

407
00:20:10,371 --> 00:20:12,999
Do you really think this is
about me waiting a few minutes?

408
00:20:14,375 --> 00:20:15,585
What's the matter?

409
00:20:15,668 --> 00:20:19,631
Aside from surgeries,
I see about 300 outpatients a day too.

410
00:20:20,506 --> 00:20:23,176
But do you know why
I still make time to date?

411
00:20:23,259 --> 00:20:25,970
Because I have a personal life.

412
00:20:26,054 --> 00:20:28,139
I want to live like a human being.

413
00:20:29,140 --> 00:20:33,603
I just want to laugh
and enjoy my time with you.

414
00:20:34,729 --> 00:20:38,274
But with you, Dam Ye-jin.
Not home shopping host Dam Ye-jin.

415
00:20:39,234 --> 00:20:40,443
But…

416
00:20:41,319 --> 00:20:44,072
I can't separate
those two that distinctly.

417
00:20:48,117 --> 00:20:51,663
Then, you can just date that job of yours
that you love so much.

418
00:21:15,186 --> 00:21:17,146
The gentleman already paid.

419
00:21:18,022 --> 00:21:20,400
Actually, it's not because of that.

420
00:21:22,318 --> 00:21:23,861
Your cutlery…

421
00:21:23,945 --> 00:21:26,322
Could I know who you bought these from?

422
00:21:32,954 --> 00:21:34,914
Hey, Mr. Hwang.

423
00:21:36,124 --> 00:21:37,500
Ms. Dam!

424
00:21:37,583 --> 00:21:39,585
You almost made me faint earlier!

425
00:21:39,669 --> 00:21:41,504
I… Oh, my gosh!

426
00:21:41,587 --> 00:21:44,757
Mr. Hwang, I found our next product.

427
00:21:44,841 --> 00:21:47,051
This is cutlery made
from premium stainless steel

428
00:21:47,135 --> 00:21:47,969
and Nordic wood.

429
00:21:48,052 --> 00:21:50,013
Both its features
and performance are amazing.

430
00:21:50,096 --> 00:21:52,682
Let's test it and get in touch
to make it our next product.

431
00:21:53,308 --> 00:21:54,142
Hang on.

432
00:21:58,771 --> 00:22:01,441
A Nordic walnut handle
that's been oiled twice

433
00:22:01,524 --> 00:22:03,776
and intricately carved
to a 1.5mm thickness…

434
00:22:04,986 --> 00:22:06,487
I can just tell how well it'll cut.

435
00:22:07,864 --> 00:22:08,698
Let's do it!

436
00:22:08,781 --> 00:22:10,074
- All right!
- All right!

437
00:22:14,495 --> 00:22:16,080
Okay. All right, then.

438
00:22:16,831 --> 00:22:17,999
I'll wait in the lobby.

439
00:22:18,750 --> 00:22:19,751
Don't be late.

440
00:22:30,386 --> 00:22:32,305
JI YUN-JI
HIT'S TOP SELLER FOR 2024

441
00:22:33,139 --> 00:22:35,308
DAM YE-JIN
HIT'S SECOND TOP SELLER FOR 2024

442
00:22:37,143 --> 00:22:38,686
This business

443
00:22:38,770 --> 00:22:39,979
is pretty cruel,

444
00:22:40,063 --> 00:22:41,189
don't you think?

445
00:22:41,272 --> 00:22:42,398
Sales aren't everything.

446
00:22:43,107 --> 00:22:45,234
But they use photo size
to show the difference.

447
00:22:46,986 --> 00:22:48,696
I heard you almost made a scene again.

448
00:22:50,364 --> 00:22:51,866
I actually did.

449
00:22:52,408 --> 00:22:54,452
We sold 230% of our target.

450
00:22:54,535 --> 00:22:55,661
That's a huge scene.

451
00:22:55,745 --> 00:22:57,872
But you're a pro in that area.

452
00:22:57,955 --> 00:23:01,501
I bring in more with one jar of cream
than you do with ten rags.

453
00:23:03,252 --> 00:23:04,587
Right.

454
00:23:04,670 --> 00:23:06,923
While you sell one, I sell ten.

455
00:23:07,465 --> 00:23:08,633
What?

456
00:23:08,716 --> 00:23:11,719
Isn't it a relief
that I don't sell cosmetics?

457
00:23:11,803 --> 00:23:13,262
Look here, Dam Ye-jin.

458
00:23:16,891 --> 00:23:18,142
Hey.

459
00:23:18,226 --> 00:23:19,602
We have plans.

460
00:23:19,685 --> 00:23:20,520
See you later.

461
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:26,818
What's the deal with Ji Yun-ji?

462
00:23:26,901 --> 00:23:29,821
Geez, she's evil to the bone.

463
00:23:29,904 --> 00:23:32,073
She insults you
instead of being a supportive senior.

464
00:23:33,074 --> 00:23:34,742
Are you being upset on my behalf?

465
00:23:34,826 --> 00:23:36,869
Damn it, I've been upset all day!

466
00:23:36,953 --> 00:23:39,205
If you do that to me again
on a live broadcast,

467
00:23:39,831 --> 00:23:41,457
regardless of our four-year friendship,

468
00:23:41,541 --> 00:23:42,917
I'm gone. Got that?

469
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,585
I got it, so you can stop.

470
00:23:45,545 --> 00:23:47,713
You don't yell at a woman
who just broke up.

471
00:23:48,714 --> 00:23:50,842
Why did you get dumped?

472
00:23:54,095 --> 00:23:56,472
I never said I got dumped.

473
00:23:57,431 --> 00:23:58,724
I mean…

474
00:23:59,934 --> 00:24:01,811
- You're so busy.
- So what?

475
00:24:01,894 --> 00:24:03,312
Everyone's busy.

476
00:24:03,396 --> 00:24:05,106
But not everyone lives like you.

477
00:24:05,189 --> 00:24:07,525
How do other people live then?

478
00:24:09,068 --> 00:24:10,987
You know,

479
00:24:11,070 --> 00:24:13,573
I work to eat chicken and beer
after clocking out.

480
00:24:14,282 --> 00:24:16,826
I smile when I think
about chicken and beer,

481
00:24:16,909 --> 00:24:19,662
and I can endure any crap
that people give me.

482
00:24:19,745 --> 00:24:21,914
That's what helps me breathe.

483
00:24:21,998 --> 00:24:23,749
Everyone has something like that.

484
00:24:23,833 --> 00:24:26,169
A lover, a celebrity they like, a hobby,

485
00:24:26,752 --> 00:24:28,462
or maybe just a restaurant they like.

486
00:24:30,339 --> 00:24:32,008
But you?

487
00:24:32,091 --> 00:24:34,552
You just never clock out of work.

488
00:24:34,635 --> 00:24:37,054
Well, it just happens
that when I'm working--

489
00:24:37,138 --> 00:24:38,890
Exactly. So why are you working?

490
00:24:39,599 --> 00:24:41,309
Don't we all work to live a decent life?

491
00:24:52,111 --> 00:24:55,031
<i>But do you know why
I still make time to date?</i>

492
00:24:55,114 --> 00:24:57,533
<i>Because I have a personal life.</i>

493
00:24:57,617 --> 00:24:59,410
<i>I want to live like a human being.</i>

494
00:25:01,287 --> 00:25:05,750
I just want to laugh
and enjoy my time with you.

495
00:25:06,417 --> 00:25:07,835
But with you, Dam Ye-jin.

496
00:25:08,753 --> 00:25:10,504
Not home shopping host Dam Ye-jin.

497
00:25:44,664 --> 00:25:47,458
DOESN'T CUT WELL ENOUGH

498
00:25:56,968 --> 00:25:58,177
PASTEL POPULAR AMONG THE YOUNG

499
00:26:48,311 --> 00:26:50,938
<i>My daughter, Ye-jin. Your health
is the most important thing.</i>

500
00:26:51,022 --> 00:26:53,232
<i>No matter how busy you are,
make sure to eat well.</i>

501
00:26:57,236 --> 00:27:01,032
Hey, I was checking the responses
for the previous Airix product.

502
00:27:01,115 --> 00:27:02,533
And for the new one, I thought…

503
00:27:32,229 --> 00:27:33,689
Okay, I'll check that right now.

504
00:27:34,607 --> 00:27:37,902
Well… Next week…

505
00:27:37,985 --> 00:27:41,113
I don't think I'll be available next week.

506
00:27:41,197 --> 00:27:43,282
How about the week after that,
on the 29th?

507
00:27:44,367 --> 00:27:47,536
I only have one meeting at 3:00 p.m.,
so I can make time in the morning.

508
00:28:11,477 --> 00:28:12,812
POEMS BY PARK JOON

509
00:28:16,691 --> 00:28:17,900
That's hot.

510
00:28:24,073 --> 00:28:25,950
The wavy rubber tip
at the top of the nozzle…

511
00:28:26,033 --> 00:28:30,204
It's suitable for all hair types,
but especially great for straight hair.

512
00:28:33,749 --> 00:28:35,251
TAKE ONLY WHEN UNABLE TO SLEEP

513
00:29:20,087 --> 00:29:23,090
GOJEUNEOK BIO

514
00:29:28,179 --> 00:29:29,221
Do you

515
00:29:30,222 --> 00:29:32,475
really want to see me lose it?

516
00:29:33,768 --> 00:29:35,561
I'm nothing

517
00:29:35,644 --> 00:29:39,190
without you or money.

518
00:29:43,861 --> 00:29:45,821
Are you trying to make me the villain?

519
00:29:45,905 --> 00:29:48,532
- I said I don't need it.
- Just use it, will you?

520
00:29:51,410 --> 00:29:53,287
So I have to just because you tell me to?

521
00:29:53,370 --> 00:29:54,288
I won't.

522
00:29:54,371 --> 00:29:57,082
Just use the new one. It'll be nice
to ride one with a new engine.

523
00:29:57,875 --> 00:29:59,084
I hate loud things.

524
00:30:00,544 --> 00:30:03,297
Tractors are supposed to be loud.

525
00:30:06,258 --> 00:30:07,384
I thought you'd like it.

526
00:30:08,886 --> 00:30:10,596
I swear, you're so difficult…

527
00:30:10,679 --> 00:30:13,307
- If that's it, I'm hanging up.
<i>- Wait.</i>

528
00:30:19,021 --> 00:30:20,606
About that thing…

529
00:30:22,441 --> 00:30:23,984
So you haven't changed your mind?

530
00:30:28,531 --> 00:30:30,533
No. Go ahead as planned.

531
00:30:55,057 --> 00:30:57,351
It's hard covering up
the bags under your eyes today.

532
00:30:57,434 --> 00:30:59,353
Are you tired?

533
00:30:59,436 --> 00:31:02,523
No, I'm at full power right now.

534
00:31:07,444 --> 00:31:10,072
That's Beauty Song's
new product, isn't it?

535
00:31:10,155 --> 00:31:13,284
Yes, I bought it since it was going viral.

536
00:31:13,367 --> 00:31:15,828
It's awesome. Just look.

537
00:31:15,911 --> 00:31:17,413
Your skin looks silky smooth.

538
00:31:17,997 --> 00:31:18,914
It's good.

539
00:31:20,875 --> 00:31:22,251
Sir, is this centered?

540
00:31:22,751 --> 00:31:24,295
- Left? Right? Okay.
- Good.

541
00:31:29,133 --> 00:31:30,467
Can you place that in the center?

542
00:31:31,051 --> 00:31:32,261
Hello.

543
00:31:41,061 --> 00:31:45,399
DAM YE-JIN'S ONLY1

544
00:31:47,401 --> 00:31:49,403
EMPLOYEES ONLY

545
00:32:02,625 --> 00:32:04,043
Hang on.

546
00:32:04,126 --> 00:32:06,045
You smoke, Mr. Hwang?

547
00:32:09,048 --> 00:32:10,299
What is it?

548
00:32:11,091 --> 00:32:12,843
Nervous about your first prime time show?

549
00:32:14,762 --> 00:32:16,347
- Well…
- I understand.

550
00:32:16,931 --> 00:32:18,265
Being a merchandiser is tough.

551
00:32:18,349 --> 00:32:21,101
People say the "MD" in merchandiser
means "must do everything."

552
00:32:21,727 --> 00:32:23,187
And they say if you're an MD at HIT,

553
00:32:23,270 --> 00:32:25,314
it means "You're making me crazy,
Dam Ye-jin."

554
00:32:27,608 --> 00:32:29,610
Spill it! What's the matter?

555
00:32:39,995 --> 00:32:41,622
WEEKLY BROADCAST SCHEDULE

556
00:32:41,705 --> 00:32:42,957
THE JI YUN-JI SHOW

557
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:44,291
Damn it!

558
00:32:45,793 --> 00:32:50,506
How about changing the background color
to violet like the brand's color?

559
00:32:50,589 --> 00:32:51,423
Violet?

560
00:32:51,507 --> 00:32:53,217
And…

561
00:32:53,300 --> 00:32:56,804
The light might reflect off the products,
so please check the angles.

562
00:32:58,180 --> 00:32:59,014
Ma'am?

563
00:33:00,224 --> 00:33:01,892
Well…

564
00:33:08,232 --> 00:33:10,275
Did you get the studios wrong?

565
00:33:10,359 --> 00:33:12,277
This is the Saturday prime time studio.

566
00:33:13,404 --> 00:33:15,739
I guess you haven't seen
the changed schedule.

567
00:33:15,823 --> 00:33:18,492
Tonight's prime time slot
has changed to The Ji Yun-ji Show.

568
00:33:18,575 --> 00:33:20,494
We're launching Beauty Song's compact.

569
00:33:21,870 --> 00:33:22,955
Beauty Song?

570
00:33:23,622 --> 00:33:24,456
Yeah.

571
00:33:42,599 --> 00:33:44,643
It seems the set hasn't been cleared yet.

572
00:33:45,310 --> 00:33:47,187
Ms. Song.

573
00:33:47,271 --> 00:33:50,816
Ms. Dam didn't see the updated schedule.

574
00:33:51,483 --> 00:33:52,609
Oh, my.

575
00:33:52,693 --> 00:33:55,404
You really haven't changed, Ms. Dam.

576
00:34:04,413 --> 00:34:05,664
Aren't you sick

577
00:34:05,748 --> 00:34:08,042
of saying "I didn't know" as an excuse?

578
00:34:10,085 --> 00:34:13,297
- Everyone, I think we should hurry.
- Yes, ma'am.

579
00:34:16,717 --> 00:34:18,177
- Let's take all these out.
- One, two!

580
00:34:19,470 --> 00:34:21,180
DAM YE-JIN'S ONLY1

581
00:34:21,263 --> 00:34:22,639
I'm sorry.

582
00:34:24,224 --> 00:34:25,309
Okay, let's proceed.

583
00:34:33,317 --> 00:34:35,110
MAKING ME CRAZY DAM YE-JIN

584
00:34:44,453 --> 00:34:46,497
ANSWER WITHIN TEN SECONDS

585
00:34:46,580 --> 00:34:48,207
Don't answer. It'll be a disaster.

586
00:34:48,290 --> 00:34:51,251
- Should I turn it off?
- No, that would be worse.

587
00:34:51,794 --> 00:34:54,088
She wouldn't go straight
to the director, would she?

588
00:34:54,630 --> 00:34:56,840
Come on. Even if she's practically
a human bulldozer,

589
00:34:56,924 --> 00:34:58,926
she'd be insane to just barge in there.

590
00:34:59,009 --> 00:35:00,094
Right?

591
00:35:11,021 --> 00:35:12,731
I didn't hear you knock.

592
00:35:12,815 --> 00:35:15,317
You're the one who skipped protocol first.

593
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:17,778
Why was the schedule changed
to The Ji Yun-ji Show?

594
00:35:17,861 --> 00:35:20,072
How could you do this
without even telling me?

595
00:35:23,367 --> 00:35:24,910
At this rate,

596
00:35:24,993 --> 00:35:27,496
we'll be crushed by CT Life Shopping
before the next quarter.

597
00:35:27,579 --> 00:35:30,165
Beauty Song's Song Myeong-hwa Compact

598
00:35:30,249 --> 00:35:32,126
was the one that boosted CT's sales.

599
00:35:32,209 --> 00:35:33,293
So if they're coming to us,

600
00:35:33,377 --> 00:35:35,712
shouldn't we offer
our prime time slot on Saturday?

601
00:35:35,796 --> 00:35:37,381
Why does it have to be my slot?

602
00:35:37,464 --> 00:35:38,715
The prime time slot

603
00:35:38,799 --> 00:35:40,634
is for best-selling products,

604
00:35:40,717 --> 00:35:42,678
not for hosts who have good sales.

605
00:35:44,513 --> 00:35:47,683
You know that beauty products
are the real moneymakers.

606
00:35:47,766 --> 00:35:48,600
Ma'am,

607
00:35:48,684 --> 00:35:53,188
our team's average target achievement rate
for the past three months is over 180%.

608
00:35:53,272 --> 00:35:55,274
And with prime time consumers,

609
00:35:55,357 --> 00:35:57,151
we'll be able to show even better results…

610
00:35:58,485 --> 00:35:59,611
That's right.

611
00:35:59,695 --> 00:36:02,322
It's the brand that both
Haeseong Duty Free and Lux Duty Free

612
00:36:03,157 --> 00:36:06,076
were desperate to get on board

613
00:36:06,160 --> 00:36:07,786
but failed to in the end.

614
00:36:09,288 --> 00:36:10,372
L'Étoile.

615
00:36:11,456 --> 00:36:14,084
We'll need a brand like that
to push out Beauty Song.

616
00:36:14,626 --> 00:36:16,003
I don't sell cosmetics.

617
00:36:17,713 --> 00:36:20,549
That clause has always
been in my contracts.

618
00:36:21,425 --> 00:36:22,593
But I guess you forgot.

619
00:36:23,427 --> 00:36:25,846
I'll find a product
that is as good as L'Étoile's.

620
00:36:25,929 --> 00:36:27,973
The Danish royal tableware
you mentioned before--

621
00:36:28,056 --> 00:36:30,601
You seem mistaken about something.

622
00:36:30,684 --> 00:36:32,853
But L'Étoile is the only brand

623
00:36:33,437 --> 00:36:36,023
that would allow you
to retake the prime time slot.

624
00:36:37,357 --> 00:36:38,233
If you can't do that,

625
00:36:38,317 --> 00:36:41,820
then your dream of hosting a show
with your name on it will end here.

626
00:36:41,904 --> 00:36:44,531
- Ma'am!
- When are you going to stop running away?

627
00:36:46,450 --> 00:36:47,951
Are you going to betray

628
00:36:48,035 --> 00:36:51,413
the partner companies, merchandisers,
and producers relying on you over this?

629
00:36:54,249 --> 00:36:56,043
The next time you enter my office,

630
00:36:56,126 --> 00:36:58,337
you'd better have
a contract with L'Étoile.

631
00:37:07,930 --> 00:37:08,764
Ms. Dam.

632
00:37:09,264 --> 00:37:10,265
Have you lost your mind?

633
00:37:10,349 --> 00:37:12,017
How could you barge in there like that?

634
00:37:12,100 --> 00:37:13,644
So what did the director say?

635
00:37:14,561 --> 00:37:16,730
What is it? What did she say?

636
00:37:16,813 --> 00:37:18,774
She said that if I want my spot back,

637
00:37:20,025 --> 00:37:21,818
I have to bring L'Étoile on board.

638
00:37:22,903 --> 00:37:24,196
- L'Étoile?
- What?

639
00:37:24,279 --> 00:37:26,114
You mean the French brand, L'Étoile?

640
00:37:26,949 --> 00:37:28,784
But Ms. Dam doesn't do cosmetics.

641
00:37:30,911 --> 00:37:32,037
That hurts.

642
00:37:33,205 --> 00:37:35,958
Damn it. How can Ms. Dong be so cruel?

643
00:37:36,041 --> 00:37:37,042
Wait!

644
00:37:37,125 --> 00:37:39,211
How in the world
is she going to bring in L'Étoile?

645
00:37:39,294 --> 00:37:40,295
I know.

646
00:38:12,584 --> 00:38:15,128
It's not like I'm a celebrity or anything.

647
00:38:15,211 --> 00:38:17,964
If word gets out that you're in Korea,

648
00:38:18,048 --> 00:38:21,801
the duty-free retailers
who sent in offers will be all over you.

649
00:38:21,885 --> 00:38:24,846
Then, our confidential information
would be exposed in no time.

650
00:38:24,929 --> 00:38:27,557
Look, no one in Korea would recognize me…

651
00:38:31,186 --> 00:38:32,395
Where are we going?

652
00:38:32,479 --> 00:38:34,397
What's trending in Korea these days?

653
00:38:34,481 --> 00:38:36,816
First, let me take you to your hotel.

654
00:38:36,900 --> 00:38:40,195
You can rest there
until your evening meeting.

655
00:38:41,321 --> 00:38:42,655
You don't mean tonight, do you?

656
00:38:43,365 --> 00:38:44,491
I do, sir.

657
00:38:44,574 --> 00:38:46,409
But I just got here from France.

658
00:38:46,493 --> 00:38:48,370
Well, the meeting
is what you came here for.

659
00:38:51,998 --> 00:38:55,043
Did you say the raw material supplier
was called Gojeuneok Bio?

660
00:38:55,919 --> 00:38:56,753
Yes.

661
00:39:10,767 --> 00:39:14,145
It's nice to meet you.
I'm Kang Mu-won, CEO of Gojeuneok Bio.

662
00:39:14,229 --> 00:39:16,940
Hello. I'm Eric Seo,
Executive Director at L'Étoile.

663
00:39:17,023 --> 00:39:18,650
Nice to meet you. Please take a seat.

664
00:39:19,484 --> 00:39:23,071
We offered very favorable terms
in the new raw material supply contract.

665
00:39:23,154 --> 00:39:24,614
Have you considered it?

666
00:39:24,697 --> 00:39:25,990
CONTRACT AMENDMENT PROPOSAL

667
00:39:32,539 --> 00:39:36,084
Of course. I considered it very carefully.

668
00:39:37,001 --> 00:39:37,836
Then--

669
00:39:37,919 --> 00:39:39,838
But I won't be able to give
the answer you want.

670
00:39:39,921 --> 00:39:42,006
I'm sorry you had to come all this way.

671
00:39:42,966 --> 00:39:44,300
To be honest,

672
00:39:44,384 --> 00:39:46,177
this is hard to understand.

673
00:39:46,261 --> 00:39:48,972
We increased
the previous order volume by five times,

674
00:39:49,055 --> 00:39:52,725
and we also adjusted the terms to be
much more favorable to Gojeuneok Bio.

675
00:39:54,561 --> 00:39:56,896
You're worried you won't be able to manage

676
00:39:56,980 --> 00:39:58,481
- the increased volume, right?
- Yes.

677
00:39:58,565 --> 00:40:01,317
Yes, I think that seems
to be the biggest concern…

678
00:40:03,945 --> 00:40:05,530
I mean, it is the biggest concern.

679
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:08,241
Then,

680
00:40:08,324 --> 00:40:11,077
we'll come up with a way
to resolve that issue.

681
00:40:11,161 --> 00:40:11,995
No,

682
00:40:12,078 --> 00:40:13,663
let me be clear about this.

683
00:40:13,746 --> 00:40:14,706
Gojeuneok Bio

684
00:40:15,582 --> 00:40:17,709
will not renew our contract with L'Étoile.

685
00:40:32,599 --> 00:40:35,602
You must be tired.
Should I take you back to the hotel?

686
00:40:35,685 --> 00:40:36,895
Mr. Cha.

687
00:40:37,604 --> 00:40:40,190
There's something strange about Mr. Kang.

688
00:40:40,815 --> 00:40:42,817
It was like he was speaking
for someone else.

689
00:40:43,359 --> 00:40:46,988
Then I'll look into Gojeuneok Bio
a bit more.

690
00:40:49,532 --> 00:40:52,994
My sister must be worried sick
that I'm slacking off here.

691
00:40:53,077 --> 00:40:57,624
Our deputy CEO, Michelle,
is especially worried about you.

692
00:41:00,251 --> 00:41:01,669
Oh, dear. It's raining.

693
00:41:04,631 --> 00:41:06,382
We should get this done quickly

694
00:41:06,883 --> 00:41:07,967
before it's too late.

695
00:41:08,885 --> 00:41:10,637
<i>The first set has sold out.</i>

696
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:11,721
<i>Oh, my!</i>

697
00:41:11,804 --> 00:41:13,848
<i>It's sold out. My gosh!</i>

698
00:41:14,432 --> 00:41:15,850
<i>It's already sold out.</i>

699
00:41:15,934 --> 00:41:20,396
<i>You know, it's only been 30 minutes
since we started the show.</i>

700
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:24,275
<i>We have an hour,</i>
<i>but it's already sold out. At this rate</i>…

701
00:41:24,359 --> 00:41:25,693
All right!

702
00:41:25,777 --> 00:41:28,238
Since it's late,
how about a late-night snack--

703
00:41:28,321 --> 00:41:30,698
What? So we can watch her show?

704
00:41:30,782 --> 00:41:32,325
<i>What do we do with our remaining time?</i>

705
00:41:32,408 --> 00:41:34,744
Why isn't this turning off? Damn it!

706
00:41:34,827 --> 00:41:36,496
<i>I am so surprised too.</i>

707
00:41:41,084 --> 00:41:42,293
Just go home now.

708
00:41:42,377 --> 00:41:43,461
Right.

709
00:41:43,545 --> 00:41:45,046
I don't even want to be

710
00:41:45,129 --> 00:41:47,006
in the same building
as Ji Yun-ji right now.

711
00:41:49,676 --> 00:41:50,510
Get up.

712
00:42:01,729 --> 00:42:03,398
<i>What's really surprising is</i>

713
00:42:03,481 --> 00:42:06,317
<i>that blotting paper
doesn't seem to stick to this at all.</i>

714
00:42:06,401 --> 00:42:08,236
<i>- Right.
- If I put a sheet</i>

715
00:42:08,319 --> 00:42:09,571
<i>of blotting paper on my face…</i>

716
00:42:09,654 --> 00:42:10,947
<i>Look. Seriously.</i>

717
00:42:11,030 --> 00:42:13,199
<i>It just falls off right away.</i>

718
00:42:14,450 --> 00:42:16,452
ACTRESS SONG MYEONG-HWA'S
BEAUTY SONG COMPACT

719
00:42:39,684 --> 00:42:41,686
- We demand compensation!
- We demand compensation!

720
00:42:41,769 --> 00:42:42,729
WE SUFFER EVERY DAY

721
00:42:47,233 --> 00:42:49,944
I'm sorry. I apologize.

722
00:42:50,737 --> 00:42:52,238
<i>My skin feels so moist.</i>

723
00:42:52,322 --> 00:42:55,658
<i>I gave away all of my blotting paper
to my friends and acquaintances.</i>

724
00:42:55,742 --> 00:42:57,368
<i>- Really?
- Yes, seriously.</i>

725
00:42:57,452 --> 00:42:58,536
<i>I see.</i>

726
00:42:58,620 --> 00:43:01,497
<i>As time passes by,</i>

727
00:43:01,581 --> 00:43:04,959
<i>we want to make our skin smooth
and gentle.</i>

728
00:43:05,043 --> 00:43:07,420
<i>When you get to your forties,
fifties, and sixties…</i>

729
00:43:34,864 --> 00:43:36,449
Stick with your usual size.

730
00:43:37,241 --> 00:43:39,661
Customer 8782 is asking about washing it.

731
00:44:46,561 --> 00:44:49,355
That's why we prepared
oil directly imported from Italy.

732
00:44:50,690 --> 00:44:52,400
Even if you put it in the washing machine…

733
00:44:54,527 --> 00:44:56,154
I'll discuss it with them right away.

734
00:44:56,237 --> 00:44:58,823
The lineup is made up of these three…

735
00:45:20,052 --> 00:45:23,222
Ms. Dam, you've already hit
the maximum dose and duration.

736
00:45:23,306 --> 00:45:25,850
If you keep overusing sleeping pills,

737
00:45:25,933 --> 00:45:27,935
<i>you may experience serious side effects,</i>

738
00:45:28,019 --> 00:45:31,189
<i>such as sleepwalking, memory loss,
and even respiratory depression.</i>

739
00:45:31,272 --> 00:45:33,733
<i>You could seriously hurt yourself.</i>

740
00:45:36,652 --> 00:45:38,821
<i>Just one pill per day.
Please stick to that.</i>

741
00:45:44,035 --> 00:45:45,661
<i>When are you going to stop running away?</i>

742
00:45:45,745 --> 00:45:48,039
<i>Aren't you sick
of saying "I didn't know" as an excuse?</i>

743
00:45:54,504 --> 00:45:55,505
We'll get ready now!

744
00:45:55,588 --> 00:45:57,590
- Excuse me.
- Don't step on that!

745
00:45:57,673 --> 00:45:58,841
Out of the way!

746
00:45:59,467 --> 00:46:00,510
Please take this out too.

747
00:46:00,593 --> 00:46:01,969
- Passing through.
- Excuse me.

748
00:46:02,678 --> 00:46:03,930
Ms. Dam?

749
00:46:04,013 --> 00:46:05,765
We're starting now. There's no time.

750
00:46:58,150 --> 00:47:02,029
MS. ANGRY EOM

751
00:47:08,369 --> 00:47:10,955
Ms. Eom, is it another
simultaneous live broadcast today?

752
00:47:11,038 --> 00:47:14,000
Why isn't she picking up her phone again?

753
00:47:14,917 --> 00:47:17,503
Is she not here yet?

754
00:47:18,087 --> 00:47:20,214
This won't do.
I'll look for a recorded segment.

755
00:47:20,298 --> 00:47:22,717
You try to do something here.

756
00:47:22,800 --> 00:47:23,884
- Do what?
- Anything.

757
00:47:23,968 --> 00:47:25,761
- Just do something.
- What…

758
00:47:25,845 --> 00:47:27,263
Hey! You little…

759
00:47:27,346 --> 00:47:28,931
- Sorry.
- Geez.

760
00:47:29,015 --> 00:47:30,266
What's wrong? Are you sick?

761
00:47:30,349 --> 00:47:31,475
Sorry, I'll go get ready.

762
00:47:31,559 --> 00:47:33,561
Hang on. Is something wrong?

763
00:47:34,103 --> 00:47:34,937
I'm fine.

764
00:47:35,021 --> 00:47:36,397
For crying out loud.

765
00:47:36,480 --> 00:47:38,190
I'm really okay.

766
00:47:39,734 --> 00:47:42,403
We hope all your days
are healthy days with Binox.

767
00:47:42,486 --> 00:47:44,488
Thank you for all of your love
and support today.

768
00:47:44,572 --> 00:47:47,408
This was your home shopping host,
Dam Ye-jin. Thank you.

769
00:47:49,869 --> 00:47:50,911
Great job!

770
00:47:57,126 --> 00:47:58,628
<i>You can't focus on just the symptoms.</i>

771
00:47:58,711 --> 00:48:00,379
<i>Real issues and relationships</i>

772
00:48:00,463 --> 00:48:02,131
<i>that you can't avoid are connected to it.</i>

773
00:48:02,882 --> 00:48:05,301
<i>There are underlying factors
behind your insomnia.</i>

774
00:48:06,135 --> 00:48:09,722
<i>To break this nightly cycle of insomnia,</i>

775
00:48:09,805 --> 00:48:12,016
<i>you have to resolve the root cause first.</i>

776
00:48:13,434 --> 00:48:15,394
- Goodbye!
- Bye!

777
00:48:15,478 --> 00:48:17,104
<i>It's time to face it now.</i>

778
00:48:18,147 --> 00:48:19,690
<i>You must figure out</i>

779
00:48:20,316 --> 00:48:22,777
<i>what is deep down inside
that's pulling you down.</i>

780
00:48:23,986 --> 00:48:25,237
Hey, don't joke around.

781
00:48:25,321 --> 00:48:26,989
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

782
00:48:27,073 --> 00:48:28,658
Get home safely.

783
00:48:34,205 --> 00:48:36,165
Mechoori!

784
00:48:41,837 --> 00:48:43,381
- Did you have a good day?
- Yeah.

785
00:48:44,548 --> 00:48:45,716
Thanks.

786
00:49:13,911 --> 00:49:15,371
- What's this?
- Striped maple extract.

787
00:49:16,122 --> 00:49:17,873
I knew you'd never drink it if I told you.

788
00:49:19,542 --> 00:49:21,168
I saw you vomiting.

789
00:49:22,211 --> 00:49:23,671
So don't complain and just drink it.

790
00:49:23,754 --> 00:49:25,715
It helps with stress-related gastritis.

791
00:49:32,847 --> 00:49:33,848
I really can't drink it.

792
00:49:35,349 --> 00:49:38,102
You don't have to bring in L'Étoile
if you don't want to.

793
00:49:39,019 --> 00:49:40,896
What about our team if I don't?

794
00:49:43,691 --> 00:49:47,445
If we get fired, we can just go to CT.

795
00:49:47,987 --> 00:49:49,822
Hey, after spending four years

796
00:49:49,905 --> 00:49:52,450
working with someone
who sells everything besides cosmetics,

797
00:49:52,533 --> 00:49:54,869
I have experience
in every field except makeup.

798
00:49:54,952 --> 00:49:57,455
You could say I'm an all-rounder.

799
00:50:02,585 --> 00:50:03,586
Do you know what this is?

800
00:50:11,635 --> 00:50:14,346
Four years ago, after our first show,

801
00:50:14,430 --> 00:50:17,266
you left this product description
behind in the studio.

802
00:50:17,850 --> 00:50:20,728
I think we reached
only about 30% of our target rate.

803
00:50:20,811 --> 00:50:23,606
Remember how we totally messed up?

804
00:50:23,689 --> 00:50:25,983
I wondered if it was a mistake
working with you,

805
00:50:26,066 --> 00:50:28,486
but the moment I saw that,
I felt relieved.

806
00:50:29,278 --> 00:50:31,906
I knew if you were this dedicated,
I could trust you.

807
00:50:33,240 --> 00:50:34,825
But now,

808
00:50:34,909 --> 00:50:38,204
you sell over 200% of our target rates.

809
00:50:38,287 --> 00:50:39,997
Seriously, aren't you proud?

810
00:50:40,873 --> 00:50:42,249
What are you trying to say?

811
00:50:43,125 --> 00:50:45,419
There are a lot of people
who trust you now.

812
00:50:45,961 --> 00:50:49,089
So you should trust yourself too.

813
00:51:30,089 --> 00:51:32,174
There's still so much left.

814
00:51:37,054 --> 00:51:38,222
That's my sister, right?

815
00:51:39,348 --> 00:51:40,182
No, it isn't.

816
00:51:41,934 --> 00:51:44,311
I'm not sure if you've heard,

817
00:51:44,395 --> 00:51:47,356
but the biggest home shopping company
in Korea is called HIT.

818
00:51:47,439 --> 00:51:50,359
It's been consistently
sending in offers since last year.

819
00:51:51,068 --> 00:51:52,903
I know HIT. They contacted you?

820
00:51:52,987 --> 00:51:55,281
Yes, it's a host named Dam Ye-jin…

821
00:51:56,073 --> 00:51:57,074
Who?

822
00:51:58,284 --> 00:52:00,244
Home shopping host Dam Ye-jin.

823
00:52:00,327 --> 00:52:04,164
It seems like HIT found out
that you're in Korea.

824
00:52:04,248 --> 00:52:06,709
- She's asking for a meeting.
- Set it up as soon as possible.

825
00:52:06,792 --> 00:52:11,130
What? But, sir, we still have to deal
with the renewal contract--

826
00:52:11,213 --> 00:52:14,341
Mr. Cha, I've been stuck here
looking at papers for a whole week.

827
00:52:14,425 --> 00:52:17,303
Don't you understand how desperate I am

828
00:52:17,386 --> 00:52:19,221
to just talk to someone?

829
00:52:19,889 --> 00:52:20,890
Don't you?

830
00:52:42,077 --> 00:52:43,287
Hi…

831
00:52:44,997 --> 00:52:46,540
I mean, hello.

832
00:52:46,624 --> 00:52:49,543
Nice to meet you.
I'm home shopping host Dam Ye-jin.

833
00:52:53,047 --> 00:52:54,798
Nice to meet you.

834
00:53:14,193 --> 00:53:15,653
I like the proposal.

835
00:53:16,862 --> 00:53:18,989
Did you read through it carefully?

836
00:53:19,073 --> 00:53:22,284
Of course. You did too, right?

837
00:53:22,826 --> 00:53:26,789
Our meeting was scheduled in a hurry,
so you could've missed something.

838
00:53:27,623 --> 00:53:30,000
Please take another good look.

839
00:53:38,467 --> 00:53:41,804
I've already reviewed it thoroughly.

840
00:53:48,060 --> 00:53:50,688
We'll review your proposal
with a positive outlook.

841
00:53:54,191 --> 00:53:58,988
I actually didn't expect our meeting
to go so smoothly like this.

842
00:53:59,530 --> 00:54:02,992
I believe HIT has been sending offers
to L'Étoile since last year.

843
00:54:03,575 --> 00:54:05,077
So could I ask the reason for this?

844
00:54:06,036 --> 00:54:09,206
Well, we also have one condition.

845
00:54:17,381 --> 00:54:18,549
So, you're saying

846
00:54:18,632 --> 00:54:22,553
we have to work with you to resolve
your raw material renewal contract?

847
00:54:22,636 --> 00:54:25,597
Yes. If you can help us
resolve this matter,

848
00:54:25,681 --> 00:54:27,307
then I'll prioritize HIT's offer

849
00:54:27,391 --> 00:54:29,393
as soon as I return to France.

850
00:54:31,520 --> 00:54:34,606
Then, I'll take responsibility
and solve this matter.

851
00:54:34,690 --> 00:54:36,525
You're accepting my proposal?

852
00:54:37,651 --> 00:54:39,737
Yes, if you promise
to come on board right now.

853
00:54:42,531 --> 00:54:44,283
I don't have much time either.

854
00:54:45,743 --> 00:54:48,787
Since we don't have much time,
why don't we proceed on two fronts?

855
00:54:48,871 --> 00:54:51,331
You focus on convincing
the CEO of Gojeuneok Bio,

856
00:54:51,415 --> 00:54:53,792
and I'll focus on convincing
the raw material farm owner.

857
00:54:53,876 --> 00:54:55,544
The farm owner? Why?

858
00:54:55,627 --> 00:54:58,714
Gojeuneok Bio cultivates
their own raw materials.

859
00:54:59,298 --> 00:55:02,843
If we get the farm owner on our side,
we'll have a better advantage negotiating.

860
00:55:03,761 --> 00:55:05,262
By the way…

861
00:55:06,889 --> 00:55:09,641
Should we officially exchange numbers now?

862
00:55:10,559 --> 00:55:11,602
Sure.

863
00:55:16,940 --> 00:55:17,983
Here.

864
00:55:44,426 --> 00:55:45,677
Gosh, my feet.

865
00:55:49,765 --> 00:55:51,016
Let's rest a bit.

866
00:55:54,144 --> 00:55:55,104
Oh, my gosh.

867
00:55:56,814 --> 00:55:57,815
Hey, perfect timing.

868
00:55:57,898 --> 00:56:01,235
Hello, Su-min.
Give me a ride to the living room.

869
00:56:01,318 --> 00:56:02,611
<i>Pardon?</i>

870
00:56:03,195 --> 00:56:04,905
- Hey, why are you turning around?
- <i>Pardon?</i>

871
00:56:04,988 --> 00:56:06,573
- Hey!
<i>- Pardon?</i>

872
00:56:06,657 --> 00:56:08,075
Hey, Su-min… Hello, Su-min!

873
00:56:08,158 --> 00:56:09,201
- Come here.
- <i>Pardon?</i>

874
00:56:09,284 --> 00:56:10,494
- Hello--
<i>- My name is Su-min.</i>

875
00:56:10,577 --> 00:56:12,871
- Hey, Su-min. Come back here.
<i>- I am not able to do that.</i>

876
00:56:12,955 --> 00:56:14,206
Hey, where are you going?

877
00:56:14,289 --> 00:56:15,624
<i>My name is Su-min.</i>

878
00:56:15,707 --> 00:56:17,084
Fine. Just go.

879
00:56:17,167 --> 00:56:18,085
<i>Pardon?</i>

880
00:56:18,168 --> 00:56:19,128
You're out.

881
00:56:19,211 --> 00:56:20,546
<i>I do not understand.</i>

882
00:56:22,131 --> 00:56:23,423
What am I doing?

883
00:56:24,049 --> 00:56:26,552
- <i>I do not understand what you are saying.</i>
- Be quiet.

884
00:56:44,289 --> 00:56:45,999
L'Étoile.

885
00:56:54,757 --> 00:56:57,135
Let's see.

886
00:57:06,436 --> 00:57:10,565
The key ingredient of the essence
seems to be WF-Mushroom.

887
00:57:10,648 --> 00:57:12,400
Find more data on this.

888
00:57:12,484 --> 00:57:15,987
<i>WF-Mushroom is the key ingredient
in La Fin Essence</i>

889
00:57:16,070 --> 00:57:19,240
<i>and makes up over 90% of the formula.</i>

890
00:57:19,324 --> 00:57:21,826
<i>It's an extract
of the white flower noori mushroom.</i>

891
00:57:23,203 --> 00:57:25,830
Can you explain more
about the white flower noori mushroom?

892
00:57:25,914 --> 00:57:28,291
<i>The white flower noori mushroom
is native to Korea,</i>

893
00:57:29,042 --> 00:57:31,794
<i>and its extract is known
for boosting skin elasticity,</i>

894
00:57:31,878 --> 00:57:34,881
<i>reducing pore size,
and providing antioxidant benefits.</i>

895
00:57:36,216 --> 00:57:38,176
I like the data.

896
00:57:38,259 --> 00:57:40,303
You're useful. You get a pass.

897
00:57:55,401 --> 00:57:57,445
HIT HOMESHOPPING

898
00:58:02,408 --> 00:58:03,493
All done.

899
00:58:32,063 --> 00:58:33,773
<i>You're heading to the farm?</i>

900
00:58:33,856 --> 00:58:35,984
Yes, I wanted to check it myself.

901
00:58:36,651 --> 00:58:38,027
<i>What's the exact address?</i>

902
00:58:39,028 --> 00:58:41,364
We only know
that it's in Deokpung Village.

903
00:58:43,950 --> 00:58:45,577
Then, I'll just go and ask around.

904
00:58:46,160 --> 00:58:48,162
There can't be many farms
that big in the country.

905
00:59:16,858 --> 00:59:19,652
From here, go straight.

906
00:59:24,991 --> 00:59:28,286
GOODBYE
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE EXIT

907
00:59:39,797 --> 00:59:41,924
Oh, no. I can't move over.

908
01:00:11,454 --> 01:00:14,415
Sir, let me pass.

909
01:00:14,499 --> 01:00:16,125
Can you move your vehicle?

910
01:00:18,461 --> 01:00:19,837
What's with him?

911
01:00:38,815 --> 01:00:41,776
Hey! I said move your car!

912
01:00:42,944 --> 01:00:44,862
It seems like you're not from around here.

913
01:00:44,946 --> 01:00:46,989
But here, we have things called rules.

914
01:00:47,073 --> 01:00:48,324
This is a one-way street.

915
01:00:48,408 --> 01:00:51,244
I've come much further in.
I have the right of way.

916
01:00:51,327 --> 01:00:52,453
This is the way out.

917
01:00:54,163 --> 01:00:57,458
Whoever can back up faster should move.
Can't you see this?

918
01:00:58,251 --> 01:01:00,044
Tractors can't reverse.

919
01:01:00,128 --> 01:01:02,922
How can tractors not reverse?
Don't be ridiculous.

920
01:01:03,005 --> 01:01:04,549
I'm not being ridiculous.

921
01:01:04,632 --> 01:01:06,968
This tractor can't reverse
because it fell into a ditch.

922
01:01:09,345 --> 01:01:10,513
Because it fell into a ditch?

923
01:01:11,723 --> 01:01:13,766
Then, this convertible
can't reverse either

924
01:01:13,850 --> 01:01:14,851
because that's uncool!

925
01:01:51,637 --> 01:01:55,349
SOLD OUT ON YOU

926
01:01:55,433 --> 01:02:01,355
THANKS TO SPECIAL GUEST PARK JI-HWAN

927
01:02:25,797 --> 01:02:27,131
<i>What happened to your ear?</i>

928
01:02:27,215 --> 01:02:29,759
{\an8}<i>If you keep loitering,
I'll report you for obstructing business.</i>

929
01:02:29,842 --> 01:02:30,718
{\an8}That tractor!

930
01:02:30,802 --> 01:02:33,513
{\an8}You're not putting her in charge
of cosmetics again, are you?

931
01:02:33,596 --> 01:02:37,099
{\an8}<i>I'm Dam Ye-jin. I don't back out
once I've made up my mind.</i>

932
01:02:37,183 --> 01:02:38,768
{\an8}Darling! Hurry and grab the chickens.

933
01:02:39,727 --> 01:02:40,561
{\an8}Hey, Changsik!

934
01:02:40,645 --> 01:02:42,688
{\an8}<i>- Why did you come here?
- I'm here for one thing.</i>

935
01:02:42,772 --> 01:02:43,981
{\an8}Make an official appointment.

936
01:02:44,065 --> 01:02:46,317
{\an8}Instead of that, I'll do it my way.

937
01:02:46,400 --> 01:02:48,444
{\an8}<i>Is this the way you were talking about?</i>

938
01:02:48,528 --> 01:02:49,654
{\an8}My goodness!

939
01:02:52,907 --> 01:02:53,991
{\an8}What's your deal?

940
01:02:54,075 --> 01:02:54,909
{\an8}Excuse me.

941
01:02:56,536 --> 01:02:57,370
{\an8}Thank you.

942
01:02:58,504 --> 01:03:00,506
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park

